[
    {
        "content": "<p>I want to work with clauses, disjunctions of literals, and I'm not sure how to do this. Concretely, here are a few things I'm unsure about:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Given a proof of <code>(a ∨ b ∨ c) ∨ (d ∨ e ∨ f)</code>, what's the best way to get a proof of <code>a ∨ b ∨ c ∨ d ∨ e ∨ f</code>, and vice versa (that is, use associativity)?</li>\n<li>Given a proof of <code>a ∨ b ∨ c ∨ d</code>, what's the best way to get a proof of <code>c ∨ a ∨ d ∨ b</code> (or any other permutation)?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I need this for <a href=\"#narrow/stream/458659-Equational/topic/1076.20!.3D.3E.203\">https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/458659-Equational/topic/1076.20!.3D.3E.203</a>, where it will probably run tens of thousands of times, so efficiency is quite important</p>",
        "id": 477104047,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729044873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>How big of clauses are you going to work with? One idea is to precompute a number of these lemmas if it's feasible.</p>",
        "id": 477104688,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729045234
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Around 9 literals. I think it'd be feasible for associativity, but not for permutations. There could be lemmas for swapping every pair, and then I could find the swaps representing the permutation</p>",
        "id": 477104960,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729045382
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Would using swaps be better than using a bunch of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Or.elim#doc\">docs#Or.elim</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Or.inr#doc\">docs#Or.inr</a>, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Or.inl#doc\">docs#Or.inl</a> ?</p>",
        "id": 477118263,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729052118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>does <code>ac_rfl</code> help?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">((</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">ac_rfl</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 477124935,
        "sender_full_name": "Timo Carlin-Burns",
        "timestamp": 1729056488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think it'd be efficient enough, but I could try to start with it, thanks</p>",
        "id": 477125137,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729056642
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Does it have an <code>ac_exact</code> variant?</p>",
        "id": 477125210,
        "sender_full_name": "Daniel Weber",
        "timestamp": 1729056679
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, calling <code>simp</code> with <code>or_comm, or_assoc, or_left_comm</code> should prove reorderings.</p>",
        "id": 477125285,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1729056706
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(That is how <code>move_add</code> works internally and it can be configured to work with <code>and/or</code>.)</p>",
        "id": 477125407,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1729056771
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think there's an <code>ac_exact</code> variant but here's a naive implementation</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">macro</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"ac_exact\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">term</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">tactic</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">`</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">tactic</span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"k\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ac_rfl</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">example</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"o\">))</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">d</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">e</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">∨</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">ac_exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
